That the same doctrine makes God the author of sin, unjust, a tyrant, a hypocrite 3 nor is it any other than interpolated Stoicism‚ Manicheism‚ Libertinism‚ and Turcism, (strez'smum.)* That it renders men secure, as being persuaded that it does not hinder the salvation of the elect, in what manner soever they live 3 and they can with safety perpetrate the most atrocious crimes. That it does not profit the reprobate, as to salvation‚ if they should truly do all the works of the saints. That by the same (doctrine) it is taught that God, by the bare and mere determination (nudo puroque arbitrio) of his will, without any respect (views intuitu) of the sin of any man, predestinated and created the greatest part of the world to eternal damnation.
